name: beta-lactamase
classes: Acting on carbon-nitrogen bonds, other than peptide bonds;
reaction: a beta-lactam + H2O = a substituted beta-amino acid [RN:R03743]
comment: A group of enzymes of varying specificity hydrolysing beta-lactams; some act more rapidly on penicillins, some more rapidly on cephalosporins. The latter were formerly listed as EC 3.5.2.8, cephalosporinase.

references.title: Penicillinase and other beta-lactamases.
references.journal: In: Boyer, P.D. (Ed.), The Enzymes, 3rd ed., vol. 4, Academic Press, New York, 1971, p. 23-46.
